# TestEngine — project context

## Stack

- **C++20**, single **`TestEngine`** target (CMake `WIN32` on Windows — `WinMain`; see `main.cpp`).
- **Build:** CMake 3.28+; build dir usually **`build`**. Details: [`BUILD.md`](BUILD.md).
- **Dependencies:** SFML, Dear ImGui + **ImGui-SFML**, **fmt** (`third-party/`). Python 3 at **configure** time (codegen).

## `src/` layout

| Area | Role |
|------|------|
| **`Engine/App/`** | Entry (`main.cpp`), `EngineInterface`, input, fonts |
| **`Engine/Core/`** | Scene, `SceneNode`, `Signal` / **`SubscriptionsHolderBase`**, reflection (`MetaClass`, `IPropertiesProvider`) |
| **`Engine/Behaviour/`** | `Behaviour` on nodes; subfolders by domain (e.g. `Physics/`) |
| **`Engine/Visual/`** | Rendering |
| **`Engine/Editor/`** | ImGui editor (hierarchy, inspector, property tree) |
| **`Engine/Simulation/`** | Simulation glue (e.g. physics) |
| **`Environments/<Name>/`** | Demos (**`Test`**, **`Pong`**); `--env=test` / `--env=pong` |
| **`Codegen/`** | Generated `*_gen.hpp` — **do not edit**; see [`property-codegen.mdc`](property-codegen.mdc) |

New `src/**/*.cpp` files are picked up on the next configure/build (`CONFIGURE_DEPENDS` glob in CMake).

## Includes

Roots: **`src/`**, **`src/Codegen/`**. Paths relative to those roots, e.g. `#include "Engine/Core/SceneNode.h"`.

## Code idioms

- **`Scene` / `SceneNode`**, **`EntityOnNode`**, **`Behaviour`**, **`IPropertiesProvider`** + codegen for inspector fields.
- **Signals:** for subscriptions tied to an owner’s lifetime, prefer **`SubscriptionsHolderBase`** + **`Subscribe(signal, handler)`**; otherwise keep an explicit **`ScopedSubscription`** member. Avoid bare **`signal.Subscribe(...)`** with no stored handle.

